\text{prove quadratic equation are continuous in }\mathbb{R}^{n}\text{ and }
\textbf{Q}_A(\vec{v})=\vec{v}^{T}\textbf{A}\vec{v}=\sum_{i}^{n}\sum_{j}^{n}\text{a}_{ij}\text{x}_{i}\text{x}_{j}\quad\text{ such as }\quad \vec{v}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}\text{ and }\textbf{A}\in\text{Mat}_{n}(\mathbb{R})
\text{We know }\sum_{i}^{n}\sum_{j}^{n}\text{a}_{ij}\text{x}_{i}\text{x}_{j}\text{ is a polynomial with respect to } \\x_1\dots x_n \text{ and is continuous on each }x_i\in\mathbb{R}
\text{But how to prove }\textbf{Q}_{A}(\vec{v})\text{ continuous }\text{ s.t }\vec{v}\in\mathbb{R}^{n}
f : \mathbb{R}^n \to \mathbb{R}^n
g: \mathbb{R}^n \to \mathbb{R}^n
a \in \mathbb{R}^n
\langle f, g\rangle(p) = \langle f(p), g(p) \rangle
